/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:78:- It treats geometry, near-Beltrami structure, and tensor effects as things to subtract away before believing a gain. That is too purity-driven for this mission. The live beyond-De-Giorgi mechanism may be hybrid rather than purely algebraic.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/selected/chain-03.md:12:- a bounded obstruction memo showing that tensor/eigenframe structure still does not operationally separate exact NS from Tao's averaged model.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/selected/chain-03.md:57:- Kill condition: if the same argument works unchanged in the averaged model, close the chain negatively.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:5:This chain is honest about the Tao filter and legitimately targets something the averaged model may destroy. That is the good part.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:9:My judgment: this is much stronger as a bounded negative audit of helical/triadic ideas than as a live route to a beyond-De Giorgi breakthrough.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:13:### Step 1 - Fix one blowup-facing scenario and one triad-level target quantity
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:17:- "Self-amplifying comparable-scale triads" and "nonlocal triad family feeding a critical norm" are not yet singular scenarios. They are generic Fourier narratives that appear in turbulence discussions whether or not they have any blowup relevance.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:18:- The chain quietly assumes that one triad family can be isolated as the operative blowup mechanism. That is a major hidden assumption. Blowup, if it exists, could depend on a wide interacting cloud of configurations rather than a single triad class.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:28:- The step assumes there is a clean "averaged-model counterpart at the same level of description." That is not automatic. Tao's averaged equation is not just "NS with slightly modified triad coefficients." The comparison can become representation-dependent and technically slippery.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:29:- Even if one writes down different helical or triad coefficients, coefficient-level nonidentity is cheap. The relevant question is whether the difference produces a sign, monotonicity, forbidden transfer, or quantitatively stronger cancellation after summing over all admissible configurations. The step does not force that distinction sharply enough.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:33:This step is especially vulnerable to prior-art overlap. Helical decomposition, Waleffe-type triad taxonomy, and helicity-selection effects are old territory. Unless the step explicitly benchmarks against known helical folklore and known non-results, it can rediscover well-known symbol asymmetries and overstate their novelty.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:39:- The listed candidates, such as same-helicity depletion and orientation-specific cancellation, are exactly the sort of mechanisms that already look interesting in spectral language and then often collapse when asked to control a norm. That makes the shortlist vulnerable to choosing what is easy to describe rather than what is live.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:41:- A bounded shortlist may be too aggressive because the only nontrivial leverage, if any exists, may come from a hybrid mechanism: helical selection plus localization plus scenario-specific concentration geometry. The chain is organized as though a pure triad-level discriminator should appear first and only later be translated. That ordering likely excludes the only plausible successes.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:53:- The expected output asks whether the mechanism can become a usable estimate, conditional criterion, or scenario exclusion. Those are very different deliverables. Lumping them together hides the fact that the route from triad geometry to each one has different failure modes.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:63:- The negative-output option is safer, but it may end up too weak to matter: "these audited helical candidates do not yield a usable lever for this audited target quantity and triad class." That is honest, but it is narrower than the chain's central premise and may have limited mission value unless calibrated against strong prior art.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:70:The chain treats "exact NS triad geometry differs from Tao-averaged geometry" as though this is already close to a breakthrough criterion. It is not. The missing ingredient is a mechanism that survives summation, localization, and dynamics. The chain acknowledges this only late.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:74:Helical decomposition and triad bookkeeping are more refined than generic Littlewood-Paley estimates, but they are still heavily spectral and harmonic-analysis adjacent. Unless the chain isolates a genuinely algebraic NS-only sign or forbidden transfer that the averaged model destroys, it risks staying inside the spirit of Tao's obstruction while believing it has escaped.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:78:Regularity failure is a time-evolution problem. This chain is mostly static at the level of interaction coefficients. There is no serious step devoted to persistence, propagation, or why the favored triad geometry would remain relevant along a near-singular evolution. That is a major omission.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:82:Helicity selection, depletion heuristics, and triad taxonomy are not fresh territory. The chain mentions candidate mechanisms that sound plausible precisely because the literature has already found them suggestive. Without an explicit prior-art benchmark early, it can mistake old spectral intuition for new mission-live structure.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:92:The central premise already assumes that the missing discriminator "may" live at the helical or triad level. That may be true, but the chain does not build in a strong competing hypothesis that the exact triad geometry is real yet irrelevant. As written, it leans toward trying to rescue a triad mechanism instead of aggressively testing whether triad structure is just a descriptive shadow of deeper geometric dynamics.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:96:The chain's fallback is a narrow negative memo about "the most natural helical and triadic candidates." That is respectable, but it may not move the mission much unless it is explicitly framed as a calibrated obstruction to an entire class of Fourier-structure attacks. Otherwise it is just another local failure report.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:106:This chain is credible only if treated as a kill-chain for triad/helical ideas: test whether exact interaction geometry yields anything stronger than descriptive spectral asymmetry, and be prepared for the answer to be no.
