/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:37:This is a real weakness. The original chain would too quickly conclude failure if Beltrami deficit alone does not imply an existing criterion. A viable route may require a hybrid observable, for example Beltrami deficit plus concentration, anisotropy, or tube-family coherence. The refined chain should allow that.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:85:This is a real issue. Because the chain sits directly in an area with substantial prior work, it needs explicit calibration against Constantin-Fefferman-Majda, later vorticity-direction coherence work, and related geometric depletion or near-Beltrami discussions before claiming novelty or NS-specificity.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:5:This is a better-designed chain than a typical speculative PDE route. It fixes a narrow object class, it names explicit kill conditions, and it is at least aware of the central failure mode: a pretty triad-level effect that disappears after reconstruction of the full equation.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:7:The problem is that the chain is still structurally biased toward finding a "distinguished" symbol-level feature before it has earned a theorem-level bottleneck. In practice, the helical-triad literature is already full of exact-looking interaction geometry that becomes weak, non-sign-definite, or irrelevant once one restores mixed triads, shell summation, and localization. So the positive route here is weak; the negative route is much stronger. If this chain produces anything honest, it is more likely to be a sharp obstruction memo than a usable regularity mechanism.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:15:- "Helical decomposition" and "triad symbol coefficients" are not yet a research commitment. They are representations of the same quadratic interaction, and switching emphasis between them can still hide opportunism.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:22:### Step 2 - Build the exact triad-interaction ledger
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:26:- A ledger of helicity signs, resonance constraints, and Leray-symbol identities is easy to compile and easy to overinterpret. Exactness at the single-triad level is cheap.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:28:- Many symbol-level structures are exact but non-actionable. Anti-symmetries, cancellation identities, and selection rules often control the algebra before summation, then wash out once one sums over geometrically large triad classes.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:33:### Step 3 - Attach one surviving triad feature to one bottleneck theorem gap
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:38:- "Choose at most one promoted triad mechanism" helps discipline, but it may also force a false picture. Some symbol-level effects are only visible as aggregate statistical bias, not as a single heroic cancellation. If the route only allows a one-feature narrative, it may either cherry-pick or prematurely discard diffuse effects.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:39:- Allowing the intended gain to be "conditional on one restricted triad family" is dangerous. Restricted families are exactly where helical intuition looks strongest and full NS relevance looks weakest. Unless the family carries a quantified proportion of the relevant transfer, this is a built-in cherry-picking loophole.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:40:- Naming prior art is necessary but not sufficient. The real risk is not just rediscovering helical decimation or shell-model folklore; it is repackaging known qualitative preferences of same-helicity or near-resonant interactions as if they were new theorem-grade control.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:48:- "Charge the full cost" is the right instinct, but the chain underspecifies the bill. It needs explicit dyadic summation, angular multiplicity, and the loss from reintroducing all mixed-helicity interactions. Otherwise the stress test stays rhetorical.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:49:- Localization is a serious threat that the chain mentions too lightly. Helical-triad structure is most transparent in global Fourier variables. Many of the hoped-for cancellations are not stable under spatial cutoffs, local energy identities, or profile decompositions. If the eventual theorem bottleneck needs localization, this step is not a side check; it is the main obstacle.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:50:- The perturbation test around favorable helicity or resonance classes is likely fatal. Full Navier-Stokes does not let one isolate clean same-helicity or near-resonant sectors for free. If the gain is only visible on a thin interaction set, then the chain is probably seeing a regime artifact, not a structural mechanism.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:51:- The classification of failure modes is sensible, but "regime-only signal" is too mild a label. For a regularity route, a mechanism that only works in a narrow spectral or helicity regime is usually already dead unless the theorem target was explicitly restricted to that regime.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:61:- The negative branch is much more credible than the positive branch. A careful memo saying "exact helical geometry creates triad-level preferences, but they are quantitatively annihilated by mixed-triad summation and localization" would be a real output. A positive proposition here would require a very unusual piece of structure, and the chain has not given reason to expect one.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:63:The final kill condition is correct but not strong enough. Vagueness about "favorable triads" should kill the chain much earlier, not only at the end.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:68:- It overestimates how much evidential weight exact single-triad geometry should carry in a full-equation problem.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:70:- It has a built-in bias toward elegant algebraic stories. Helical-triad routes are especially vulnerable to mistaking symbolic sharpness for analytic control.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:77:What is weak is the underlying bet. The exact Leray-projected helical symbol has been studied enough that one should start from a presumption of obstruction, not a presumption that a hidden triad feature is waiting to unlock a theorem gap. This route should therefore be run mainly as an obstruction-extraction program. If it is evaluated as a positive regularity route, it is probably overrated.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-03.md:32:Navier-Stokes-specific structure is doing work and why Tao-style averaged models
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/MISSION.md:11:- The Lamb vector L = ω × u generates the CZ-lossy pressure piece. For Beltrami flows (L = 0), CZ loss vanishes — but mechanism doesn't survive even 1% perturbation from Beltrami alignment.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/MISSION.md:64:5. **Local Beltrami structure near vortex tubes.** Exact Beltrami kills CZ loss entirely (β_eff → 1.0). The mechanism requires >98% global alignment. But vortex tube cores are locally near-Beltrami. A conditional result using LOCAL Beltrami deficit (restricted to high-|ω| regions) might work — connecting to Constantin-Fefferman geometric criteria.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/MISSION.md:72:### What the Tao filter requires
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/final-decider.md:30:Chain 02 is the best adversarial test of exact Navier-Stokes interaction geometry and the most Tao-sensitive branch in the portfolio. Its novelty ceiling is real. But the positive route is still too contingent on a very specific outcome: one explicit helical feature must survive shell summation, mixed-helicity restoration, and localization with enough margin to matter at theorem scale. That makes its presentable-result odds slightly worse, and its execution risk higher, than Chain 01.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selector.md:8:4. Chain 04 - Local Beltrami Deficit To Geometric Criterion Bridge
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selector.md:16:Chain 02 stays in because it is the cleanest adversarial test of genuinely Navier-Stokes-specific algebra. It attacks the Tao screen at the exact Leray-symbol and helical-triad level, so even a negative result is informative: it can show that the exact triad geometry becomes cosmetic after honest summation or localization. That makes it both sharply differentiated from Chain 01 and high value on failure.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/selector.md:18:Chain 03 stays in because it preserves the strongest pressure-adjacent live lead without sliding back into the dead coefficient-shrinkage architecture. It is materially different from Chain 02: the unit of attack is not Fourier triads but the full stretching mechanism `S omega . omega` together with pressure-Hessian debt. It is also likely to produce a calibrated obstruction even if it does not promote to proposition scale, which makes it a strong third slot.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/mission-context.md:19:- The Lamb vector L = ω × u generates the CZ-lossy pressure piece. For Beltrami flows (L = 0), CZ loss vanishes — but mechanism doesn't survive even 1% perturbation from Beltrami alignment.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/mission-context.md:72:5. **Local Beltrami structure near vortex tubes.** Exact Beltrami kills CZ loss entirely (β_eff → 1.0). The mechanism requires >98% global alignment. But vortex tube cores are locally near-Beltrami. A conditional result using LOCAL Beltrami deficit (restricted to high-|ω| regions) might work — connecting to Constantin-Fefferman geometric criteria.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/mission-context.md:80:### What the Tao filter requires
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/mission-context.md:119:from admissible NS data, in a way that Tao's averaged model would not preserve?
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/mission-context.md:152:- Action: name the candidate NS-specific ingredient if one exists, and separate it from generic harmonic facts that Tao's averaged model should preserve.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/mission-context.md:265:Its core problem is that the missing bridge is also the main difficulty: local near-Beltrami or alignment observables do not obviously control the full stretching quantity, especially the nonlocal remainder. That makes the branch valuable, but comparatively fragile. Its best negative result is useful, though still harder to secure cleanly than Chain 01's shell-based obstruction.
