/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:64:- There is partial prior-art redundancy. Without a hard Beltrami-to-criterion bridge, the chain collapses back into known Constantin-Fefferman style regularity conditions plus suggestive tube language.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:65:- There is also structural bias toward a geometry-first conclusion. The premise assumes the averaged model destroys "fine vortex geometry," but the chain never identifies which exact geometric property is mathematically absent under averaging. That leaves too much room for confirmation bias.
